Deutscher Liederhort

The Deutscher Liederhort is a collection of 1700 German folk songs. The songs were originally collected by Ludwig Erk and later edited by Franz Magnus Böhme. Helmuth Schaffrath digitized the songs.

Issues

  • Unknown sources

    The last songs in this collection have a different catalogue number and indeed do not appear to be in Erk & Böhme volumes. From deut2243.krn onwards, catalogue numbers are of the form L0035A

  • Different titles

    The titles are actually incipits. The Erk & Böhme volumes use different titles, as you can see in the scans; volume 1, volume 2 and volume 3
